textAnnotations.description:
GEOGRAPHICAL SEC.. GEN. STAFF
- MAP ROOM
Recd. 27 SEP. 1913
MATERIAL.BR.E.AF. 227
Notes page 4
West of the Nakwai and Lobor mountains the country presents a
different aspect; consequently the types of fauna differ. Here first
in this part of Uganda, one enters the range of the Jackson Hartebeeste
and along the banks of the Naam (Udat?) river, Uganda cob (Cobus Thomasi)
were found in some numbers.
It should be noted that the Lobor and Nakwai hills present a far
more well defined dividing line as regards the country on either side
than does the Maroto and the hills to the north of it. In the case of
the latter, the country, fauna and flora, &c., only exhibit very slight
differences on either side of the watershed. West of the Nakwai and
Lobor, however, an entirely different set of conditions prevails, both
as regards the appearance of the country, the fauna and flora, and even
the inhabitants.
Many zoological specimens of great interest were obtained, including
some 700 species of birds and 400 of small mammals. These will be
classified and a report issued on the subject by the British Museum.
Hence it is not considered necessary to make any detailed observation
on the matter here.
It should be mentioned, however, that'tse-tsel fly were found on
the Kozibiri - variety apparently Glossina Longipennis - but these
were very few in number and only near the spring at Natapara.
It came somewhat as a surprise to find them in such dry, barren)
country, though doubtless in the rainy season, when all the watercourses
are full, they probably occur in some numbers. With the exception of
this spot, no 'fly were seen the whole way from B.E.A. to Nimule. There
is, however, no doubt that they exist along the Kerio and Turkwel rivers
in places, for the natives never allow their stock to remain any length
of time near the river itself, always camping well away from it as soon
as they have been watered.
The well known Nimule-Gondokoro road was found Swarming with 'fly!
in many places.
WOMAT/AFR/BEA/227/2/5
Womat 86
